<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Hold My Pet API</title>
  </head>
  <body
    style="
      height: 95vh;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      justify-content: center;
      margin-left: 20%;
      background-color: whitesmoke;
    "
  >
    <div
      style="
        background-color: white;
        width: max-content;
        padding: 3em 3em 3em 3em;
        border: 1px solid black;
        border-radius: 5px;
        box-shadow: 5px 5px black;
      "
    >
      <h1>Welcome...</h1>
      <h2 style="font-size: 4em">Hold my pet API</h2>
      <p><strong>What is Hold my pet ?</strong></p>
      <p>
        Well in a nuteshell, It is a service that helps you find a caretaker for
        <br />
        your pet while you're away from them
      </p>
      <div
        style="
          margin-top: 3em;
          background-color: whitesmoke;
          padding: 1em 1em 1em 1em;
          border-radius: 3px;
          border: 1px solid black;
        "
      >
        <p>Currently supported actions</p>
        <ul
          style="
            display: flex;
            list-style: none;
            padding-left: 0;
            justify-content: space-around;
          "
        >
          <li><a href="/pets">view all pets </a></li>
          <li><a href="/create">Create a pet </a></li>
          <li><a href="/pets">view a pet </a></li>
          <li><a href="/delete">Delete a pet </a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <p style="color: gray">
        !! To view a single pet out of the whole db add it ID after the /pets
        route i.e "/pets/:id"
      </p>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
